-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Wed Jun 25, 2014 05:59AM EDT
-- None



June 25 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1000 GMT on Wednesday:

** Greek telecoms company OTE <OTEr.AT> said it was in preliminary talks with the main shareholder of a small rival, Forthnet <FORr.AT>, to buy its subscription television operations. [ID:nL6N0P61WA]  ** Abu Dhabi's state-owned Etihad Airways said it had agreed principal terms and conditions to buy a 49 percent stake in Italy's loss-making airline Alitalia [CAITLA.UL]. [ID:nL6N0P6214]  ** Malaysia Airlines is not in talks with any other airline to help its planned restructuring as the loss-making carrier seeks to turn around a slump in business since the disappearance of Flight MH370 last March, its chief executive said. "No, we are not," Malaysian Airline System Bhd's (MAS) <MASM.KL> CEO Ahmad Jauhari told reporters. [ID:nK7N0P6000]  ** Telefonica Deutschland <O2Dn.DE> said it had agreed a deal with small rival Drillisch <DRIG.DE> as part of its efforts to obtain regulatory clearance for its 8.6 billion euro ($117 billion) takeover of KPN's <KPN.AS> German business, E-Plus. [ID:nL6N0P61B1]  ** Airbus <AIR.PA>, Europe's largest aerospace group, plans to sell its engineering unit Cimpa, French financial daily Les Echos said on Wednesday. The paper said Cimpa, which employs 940 staff and had 2012 sales of 100 million euros ($136 million), was no longer a strategic asset for the group. [ID:nL6N0P61I0]  ** The French state has raised about 1.5 billion euros with the sale of a 3.1 percent stake in gas and power group GDF Suez <GSZ.PA>, the finance and economy ministries said in a joint statement on Wednesday. [ID:nWEB00ORZ]  ** An Australian tribunal overturned a competition regulator's decision to block power supplier AGL Energy Ltd <AGK.AX> from buying two power stations from the New South Wales government, clearing the A$1.5 billion ($1.41 billion) deal to proceed. [ID:nL4N0P61KC]  ** Gas-to-liquid technology developer Velocys Plc <VLSV.L> has acquired U.S.-based Pinto Energy for an undisclosed sum, the British company said. [ID:nL6N0P61DE]   ** Australia's New South Wales state government canceled the privatization of its electricity metering businesses after it only attracted two conditional final offers which it said "didn't stack up". [ID:nL4N0P61DV]  ** China Vanke Co Ltd <000002.SZ> <2202.HK>, the country's largest residential property developer, said on Wednesday it was in talks with global investors, including funds and real estate peers, to sell a strategic stake. [ID:nH9N0OL05B]  ** Australian property company Lend Lease Corp <LLC.AX> said it had sold its interest in Bluewater Shopping Centre to Land Securities Group PLC <LAND.L> for 696 million pounds ($1.2 billion), boosting its 2014 earnings by more than 45 percent. [ID:nL4N0P54R5]  ** Electronics retailer Best Buy Co <BBY.N> is looking at a sale of or partnership for its Chinese business to better focus on its U.S. business, the Wall Street Journal reported citing people familiar with the matter. The company could get about $300 million from its Chinese business, where it operates under the names Five Star and Best Buy Mobile, the report said. [ID:nL4N0P54OL]  ** Lagardere SCA's <LAGA.PA> Hachette Book Group said it would buy Perseus Books Group, keeping the books business of the sixth-largest U.S. publisher and selling the client services businesses to Ingram Content Group. [ID:nL4N0P54GF]  ** Aetna Inc <AET.N>, the third largest U.S. health insurer, is exploring a sale of some of Coventry Health Care Inc's assets worth as much as $1.5 billion, according to people familiar with the matter, a year after it acquired its rival for $5.6 billion. [ID:nL2N0P51BA]  ** U.S. healthcare information company IMS Health Holdings Inc <IMS.N> said on Tuesday it would buy certain businesses from French healthcare software company Cegedim <CGDM.PA> for about $520 million in cash. [ID:nL4N0P546Y]  ** Energy Future Holdings on Tuesday rejected an unsolicited $2.3 billion restructuring plan by NextEra Energy Inc <NEE.N> that would have given the alternative energy group a large stake in Energy Future's power lines unit, according to court filings. [ID:nL2N0P51FQ]  ($1 = 1.0639 Australian Dollars)